'''Kawata Jinja''' (川田神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|de|Shinto-Schrein|ja|神社|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Shiga Prefecture|de|Präfektur Shiga|ja|滋賀県|12=draft}}{{ill|Kōka|de|Kōka|ja|甲賀市|12=draft}}.

== Deities ==
* {{ill|Ame-no-Yakawa|de|Ame-no-Yakawa|ja|天湯河板挙|lt=Ame-no-Yakawa|lt_ja=天湯川桁命|lt_de=Ame-no-Yakawa|12=draft}} – Ancestor deity of the Tottori-no-Muraji
* Amekawatana no Mikoto  
(Enshrined together)  
* {{ill|Ame-no-Koyane|de|Ame-no-Koyane|ja|天児屋根命|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Onamuchi no Mikoto|de|Onamuchi no Mikoto|ja|大己貴命|12=draft}}

== Shrine Crest ==
* Trailing wisteria (下り藤)

== History ==
According to tradition, it was founded during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Suinin|de|Kaiser Suinin|ja|垂仁天皇|12=draft}}. Listed as a {{ill|Myojin Taisha|de|Myojin Taisha|ja|名神大社|12=draft}} in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|de|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|12=draft}}, it is one of the ''ronsha'' (theories) regarding that identification. In the 11th year of {{ill|Kyōhō|de|Kyōhō|ja|享保|12=draft}} (1726), the shrine was elevated to Shōichii (正一位) in {{ill|Shinkai|de|Shinkai|ja|神階|12=draft}}. It served as the ''sōja'' of {{ill|Kurata-shō|de|Kurata-shō|ja|蔵田荘|12=draft}}. In the 9th year of {{ill|Meiji|de|Meiji-Zeit|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|12=draft}} (1876), it was designated a ''sonsha'' ({{ill|village shrine|de|Dorfschrein|ja|村社|12=draft}}), then became a ''gōsha'' ({{ill|town shrine|de|Ortschrein|ja|郷社|12=draft}}) in the 17th year (1884). In the 11th year of {{ill|Shōwa|de|Shōwa-Zeit|ja|昭和|12=draft}} (1936), it was raised to the status of {{ill|prefectural shrine|de|Präfekturschrein|ja|県社|12=draft}}.

== Festivals ==
* Main Festival
: Held on April 25.
* Koshiki Ageya Festival (Yōya Matsuri)

== Subsidiary Shrine ==
* Tenman-gū

